WorldStage Newsonline– President Muhammadu Buhari has described his late metal-work teacher in Katsina Secondary School, Sanda Kaita, as a man of highest character. The late Kaita was Magajin Rogo of Katsina and a retired school administrator. In a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, the president described his late metal-work teacher in Katsina Secondary School as a man of highest character. Buhari stated that Kaita will be remembered for his efforts to inculcate hard work and technical skills in his students. He said: “He was a committed and an inspirational educationist. “Our prayers go out to the family of the bereaved; to the government and people of Katsina state over this irreparable loss. “May his soul rest in peace.”